				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I must say that I am out raged by not only the necromancers and druids coming in here and bragging, shoveing thier wait around. But thier stupidity. I'm also sleepy, so expect alot of typos<BR>
<BR>
For the first thing to make clear. Dwarves are not the serious mean type people. They are happy, drinking, dancing short people who love a good time. To the DE that said &quot;We have higher dex char and int! Woot beat that! :P&quot;. As I said, what an idiot. CHA *ONLY* affects TWO things 1 - The general price (Along with faction) a merchant pays you for an item. 2 - Your ability to cast an enchantment spell on an mobs without it being resisted. I'm also sorry buddy, but we have 90DEX while you have 75 (85 for necros as a base). And you Erunites who say INT helps skills, lol. I'm still laughing. Let me just sum it up here: DEX affects your ranger and weapon skills and how they raise. The only thing DEX does if you're a caster it will make you see the &quot;You regain your concentration and continue castong&quot; but it still doesn't mean high DEX will make you be able to cast without interupptions, not INT. For warriors and pallies, INT is only useful for trade skills and a few other skills. Having high intel is nice, but when you're getting pounded by a mob, you can be the smartest mofo in the world - but you're still dead. Yea, we're short, so what? I like being short, I never need shrink potions and if I wasn't short I couldn't have my surname, Kneebasher =). And yes, I won't sit here and say druids suck, because they ARE the best solo'ist class int the game. But for sake I have to agree, couldn't you gain your xp somewhere else besides are citizens? Oh well, one day the faction will change and you'll go kos for you laziness. <BR>
<BR>
To say all that I said and make it short - You can have the highest intel in the world, if you're an idiot irl, you're an idiot in game. Must suck to have your EQ character smarter than you huh?<BR>
<BR>
Kexden of Prexus<BR>
Warrior of the Underfoot<BR>
Current affiliate of Keepers of the Faith and personel friend of Louie, the greatest warrior ever! (And I can back up &quot;the greatest warrior ever&quot; so far he's won almost all the warrior based GM events on Prexus.)
